# Dashboard Job Section — Complete Analysis

## Quick Answer: Is It Live?

| Tab | Auto-Refreshes? | Interval | Live? |
|-----|-----------------|----------|-------|
| **Job Done** | ❌ No | — | **Not live.** You must change filters or click refresh |
| **Running** | ✅ Yes | Every **15 seconds** | **Yes — live** while the tab is active |
| **Scheduled** | ❌ No | — | **Not live.** You click the Refresh button manually |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **None of the three tabs use WebSockets or server-sent events.** They all use standard HTTP polling via React Query. There is no "push" from the server — the frontend always initiates requests.

---

## How Each Tab Works — End to End

### Tab 1: Job Done (Past Runs)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant React as Dashboard.jsx
    participant RQ as React Query
    participant API as GET /api/dashboard/stats
    participant DB as MSSQL (Jobs_Details table)

    User->>React: Opens Dashboard (default tab)
    React->>RQ: useQuery('stats', appliedFilters)
    Note over RQ: enabled: activeTab === 'done' ✅
    RQ->>API: GET /api/dashboard/stats?type=day&date=2026-03-02
    API->>DB: CTE query on Jobs_Details
    DB-->>API: Rows (grouped by job_id, RunGroupID)
    API-->>RQ: JSON { totalExecutions, jobGroups, ... }
    RQ-->>React: Render stats cards + charts + tree

    User->>React: Changes date filter to March 1
    React->>RQ: queryKey changes → ['stats', {type:'day', date:'2026-03-01'}]
    Note over RQ: Key changed → automatic refetch
    RQ->>API: GET /api/dashboard/stats?type=day&date=2026-03-01
    API->>DB: CTE query with new date
    DB-->>API: New data
    RQ-->>React: Re-render with new data
```

**When does it fetch?**

| Trigger | Fetches? | Why |
|---------|----------|-----|
| Page loads (first visit) | ✅ | Initial query, tab defaults to `'done'` |
| Change date filter | ✅ | `appliedFilters` change → `queryKey` changes → auto-refetch |
| Change client filter | ✅ | Same — `queryKey` changes |
| Switch away then back to this tab | ⚠️ Only if stale | `staleTime: 30000` (30s) — if data is <30s old, uses cache |
| New job inserted in DB by someone else | ❌ | No auto-refresh. Must change filter or reload page |
| Click "Insert New Jobs" button | ✅ After 1s | Calls `refetch()` after a 1-second delay |
| Browser tab regains focus | ❌ | `refetchOnWindowFocus: false` in global config |

**What SQL does it run?**

A 4-level CTE query on `dbo.Jobs_Details`:
1. **JobGroups** — groups steps into runs using `SUM(CASE WHEN step_id = 0 ...)` window function
2. **RunDiagnostics** — aggregates per run: timestamps, duration, success/fail/cancel step lists
3. **FinalClassification** — classifies each run as Success/Failed/Cancelled
4. **FullAnalysis** — extracts "invoked by" and "stopped by" usernames from execution messages

**What data comes back?**

```
{
  totalExecutions: 45,
  successCount: 38, failedCount: 5, cancelledCount: 2,
  successRate: 84.4, failedRate: 11.1, cancelledRate: 4.4,
  activeClients: 7,
  jobsByClient: [{ client_name: "Kowa", job_count: 12 }, ...],
  jobsByStatus: [{ status: "Success", count: 38 }, ...],
  clientStatistics: [{ clientName: "Kowa", totalExecutions: 12, ... }],
  jobGroups: [{
    jobName: "Expense_Report_Audit_Kowa",
    clientName: "Kowa",
    date: "2026-03-02",
    runs: [{
      status: "Success",
      runTimeStart: 83000, runTimeEnd: 83245,
      totalDuration: 245,
      invokedBy: "System",
      failedSteps: null,
      successSteps: "Step1, Step2, Step3",
      ...
    }]
  }]
}
```

