## React Query Configuration Summary

### Global Config ([App.jsx](file:///c:/Users/afzal.sharif/OneDrive%20-%20Qordata/Desktop/visual/ema/frontend/my-app/src/App.jsx))

```js
const queryClient = new QueryClient({
  defaultOptions: {
    queries: {
      refetchOnWindowFocus: false,  // ← No refetch when browser tab regains focus
      retry: 1,                     // ← Only 1 retry on failure
    },
  },
});
```

### Per-Query Config ([Dashboard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/afzal.sharif/OneDrive%20-%20Qordata/Desktop/visual/ema/frontend/my-app/src/pages/Dashboard/Dashboard.jsx) lines 225-248)

| Query | queryKey | staleTime | refetchInterval | enabled |
|-------|----------|-----------|-----------------|---------|
| **Job Done** | `['stats', appliedFilters]` | 30s | ❌ None | `activeTab === 'done'` |
| **Running** | `['runningJobs']` | 10s | ✅ **15s** | `activeTab === 'running'` |
| **Scheduled** | `['scheduledJobs']` | 60s | ❌ None | `activeTab === 'scheduled'` |

### What `staleTime` and `refetchInterval` Mean

- **`staleTime`**: How long fetched data is considered "fresh". During this window, switching tabs won't trigger a new API call — the cached data is used instantly.
- **`refetchInterval`**: If set, the query automatically re-fetches on this timer while `enabled` is `true`. **Only Running Jobs has this.**
- **`enabled`**: The query only fires when this is `true`. When you switch tabs, the other queries are disabled.
- **`keepPreviousData`** (Job Done only): While fetching new data, the old data stays visible (no flash of empty state).

---

## Timeline: What Happens When You Use the Dashboard

```
USER OPENS /jobs page
  └─ activeTab = 'done' (default)
  └─ appliedFilters = { type: 'day', date: '2026-03-02' }
  └─ API HIT → GET /api/dashboard/stats?type=day&date=2026-03-02
  └─ Stats, charts, and job tree render

USER CLICKS "Running" TAB
  └─ activeTab = 'running'
  └─ Job Done query: DISABLED (stops)
  └─ Running query: ENABLED → API HIT → GET /api/dashboard/running
  └─ 15s timer starts → AUTO-REFRESHES every 15 seconds
  └─ Live dot + "Auto-refreshes every 15s" shown in UI

  ⏱ 15s later → API HIT → GET /api/dashboard/running (automatic)
  ⏱ 30s later → API HIT → GET /api/dashboard/running (automatic)
  ...continues while tab is active...

USER CLICKS "Scheduled" TAB
  └─ activeTab = 'scheduled'
  └─ Running query: DISABLED (15s timer stops!)
  └─ Scheduled query: ENABLED → API HIT → GET /api/dashboard/scheduled
  └─ No auto-refresh — static until you click Refresh

USER CLICKS BACK TO "Job Done" TAB
  └─ Scheduled query: DISABLED
  └─ Job Done query: ENABLED
  └─ If last fetch was <30s ago → uses cache (no API call)
  └─ If last fetch was >30s ago → API HIT → refetch

USER CHANGES DATE FILTER (while on Job Done)
  └─ appliedFilters changes → queryKey changes
  └─ New queryKey has no cache → API HIT immediately
  └─ "Updating..." indicator shown while fetching
  └─ Old data stays visible (keepPreviousData: true)
```

---

## Summary: When New Data Appears

| Scenario | Job Done | Running | Scheduled |
|----------|----------|---------|-----------|
| Someone inserts a new job in DB | Not seen until filter change or page reload | Seen within 0-15s (auto-poll) | Not seen until Refresh click |
| You click "Insert New Jobs" button | Refetches after 1s delay ✅ | N/A | N/A |
| Job starts executing on server | N/A | Appears within 0-15s ✅ | N/A |
| Job finishes executing | N/A | Disappears within 0-15s ✅ | N/A |
| New schedule is created in SQL Agent | N/A | N/A | Not seen until Refresh click |

> [!TIP]
> **Only the "Running" tab is truly live.** The other two tabs require user interaction (filter change or manual refresh) to show new data.
